inlineContent.text: A dashboard scene manages the display of your navigation app’s dashboard window on the CarPlay Dashboard, and notifies its delegate—an object that conforms to

—about scene life-cycle events. Use the dashboard controller the scene provides to supply shortcut buttons to display when there’s no active navigation session, further customizing you app’s presence on the CarPlay Dashboard.
You don’t create an instance of the dashboard scene directly. Instead, you specify the name of the class as part of the CarPlay Dashboard scene configuration that you add to your
file—see the example below—or that you return from your app delegate’s
